    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Inorganic, semiopaque, permanent pigment made of cobalt phosphate or cobalt arsenite, the latter of which is poisonous. Nontoxic cobalt phosphate is presently used to create this pigment.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047814/Mayer, Dictionary of Art Terms and Techniques (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種無機、半透明的耐久性顏料，以鈷磷酸鹽或亞砷酸鈷製成，後者具毒性，現改用無毒的鈷磷酸鹽來製造鈷紫。 </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
